SEARCH

All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ArgumentParser
The ArgumentParser class is responsible for parsing command line arguments from a given input string.
AudioManager
The AudioManager class handles audio playback and volume control for the application.
Board
The Board class represents a game board consisting of a 2D array of cells.
ButtonAction
Represents a customizable button with action listener and hover effects.
Cell
The Cell class represents a single cell on the game board.
CellButton
Represents a cell button in the Tic-Tac-Toe game that players can click to place their symbols.
Controller
The Controller class is responsible for managing the game flow and handling user input for the console-based game.
Game
The Game class implements the GameInstance interface and manages the game logic, including initializing the game board and players, starting the game, and handling player turns.
GameFrame
Represents the main game frame for the Tic-Tac-Toe application, managing the game board and UI elements.
GameInstance
The GameInstance interface defines the contract for game instances, specifying the essential operations required to manage a game.
GameState
Represents the various states of the game.
InvalidNameException
Custom exception class to handle invalid names.
LabeledTextField
A custom panel that combines a JLabel and a JTextField for a labeled text input field.
LeaderBoard
The LeaderBoard class displays a leaderboard of player scores in a table format.
MainMenu
The MainMenu class represents the main menu of the application, allowing users to navigate to different functionalities such as starting a new game, continuing an existing game, viewing the leaderboard, adjusting options, and exiting the application.
MessageBox
The MessageBox class provides utility methods for displaying various types of message dialogs, including information messages, warning messages, error messages, confirmation dialogs, and input dialogs.
OptionsPanel
The OptionsPanel class is responsible for displaying and managing the game's settings options, including audio settings, appearance settings, and display settings.
Player
The Player class represents a player in the game.
PlayersList
The PlayersList class manages a list of players in the game.
Validator
The Validator class provides validation methods for game settings, including board size and player details.
Validator.ValidationStatus
Enum representing validation status outcomes for the game setup.
Window
The Window class serves as an abstract base for all game windows.
